# Do not regenerate the demo video

Agents must **not** regenerate, re-record, or commit `demo/diff-tool-python-demo.mp4`.

## What to skip

- Do **not** run `pixi run demo-video` as part of a change
- Do **not** treat an outdated demo video as blocking or required follow-up work
- Do **not** embed or regenerate the demo MP4 unless the user **explicitly** asks
  to see or refresh the recording

## What is still fine

- Editing `demo/*.tape`, `demo/key-hints.ass`, or sample files when those assets
  themselves are part of the requested change
- Leaving the checked-in `demo/diff-tool-python-demo.mp4` unchanged even if the
  TUI behavior diverges from the recording
- Mentioning that README.md embeds `demo/diff-tool-python-demo.mp4` only when
  the user asks about the demo

The `pixi run demo-video` task remains available for humans who want a fresh
recording locally; it is not part of the agent deliverable or CI.
